data.description: Nestled in the beloved Shepherd Historic District, this stunning Tudor revival home was built in 1934 and brims with charm, comfort and possibility. Thoughtfully updated to embrace modern conveniences, it maintains its original character. The graceful curves of the porch invite guests into your stunning formal living room, splendid with its crystal chandelier, coved ceilings and smooth, rounded fireplace. The formal dining room boasts its own chandelier and coved ceilings and leads into the gorgeously updated kitchen where you’ll find a breakfast nook, continuing hardwood floors, a dry bar with beverage fridge, white cabinetry and countertops and stainless steel appliances. A spacious second living area is just through the kitchen -- perfect for cozy movie nights. A hallway lined with darling built-in storage leads to the three bedrooms on the ground floor. There is a classic, original pink and black tiled hall bathroom and an ensuite black and white bath with shower off of the NE bedroom providing an option for a second primary suite. The second floor primary suite is expansive with gleaming hardwood floors, a walk-in closet and a fully tiled bathroom with spa tub, separate shower and vanity. The private backyard features a shady, paved entertaining space and an oversized garage with a self contained 2-bed, 1-bath apt ready to be finished out! This space could have amazing potential as a rental, an office suite, art studio or incredible guest quarters! Shepherd is a hidden gem with its own park, quiet streets that don't pass through, feeder for coveted Cleveland Elementary, and just blocks from many of OKC's most desirable spots to dine, shop, and play!
